# Sales Analytics Pipeline — Excel + Python + MySQL + Power BI

## Project Overview
An end-to-end data pipeline project built to demonstrate real-world data workflow:
raw Excel data → Python cleaning → MySQL storage → Power BI dashboard.

## Business Problem
A sales team tracking orders across 4 regions and 5 product categories needed
a reliable, refreshable dashboard — not a static spreadsheet updated manually each month.

## Tools & Technologies
| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Python (pandas) | Data loading, cleaning, transformation |
| SQLAlchemy + PyMySQL | Python-to-MySQL database connection |
| MySQL | Cleaned data storage (single source of truth) |
| Power BI | Interactive dashboard and visualisation |
| Excel | Raw data source |

## What I Did
1. Loaded raw sales data (520 rows, 7 columns) from Excel into Python
2. Cleaned data: removed 38 duplicate rows, validated datatypes
3. Engineered 3 new columns: Profit, Year, Month
4. Pushed 482 clean rows into MySQL database (salesdb → sales_data table)
5. Connected Power BI to MySQL and built interactive dashboard

## Dashboard KPIs
- Total Sales: ₹20M
- Total Profit: ₹5M
- Average Profit Margin: 25.09%
- Sales trend by Month (2023–2024)
- Profit breakdown by Region (North, South, East, West)
- Sales by Product (Printer, Tablet, Laptop, Monitor, Mobile)

## Key Learning
Storing cleaned data in MySQL instead of a flat CSV means the Power BI dashboard
refreshes automatically when the Python pipeline reruns — no manual file management.

